<headline>Special Weather Statement issued February 14 at 3:29AM EST  by NWS Charleston</headline>
<description>Early morning snowfall may have created some slick spots to
roadways, especially if left untreated. Even though snowfall
amounts were minimal, along with below freezing temperatures, any
leftover moisture will have froze overnight and could also add to
possible hazardous spots.
The snow may continue into the morning commute in certain areas
which can cause decreased visibility and slippery road conditons,
especially over higher terrain. Allow extra time, slow down and
allow extra space between you and the vehicle ahead of you. Avoid
sudden breaking, accelerating and turning as much as possible.</description>
